Where food fairs will be held this weekend in Kiev. Addresses
02 Nov 2019, 09:30 by Daria Kunets
The first weekend of November in Kiev will host traditional food fairs. This was reported by the press service of the Kyiv City State Administration.
Saturday November 2
Goloseevsky district - st. Pankovskaya; st. Goloseevskaya, 4-10;
Darnytskyi district - st. Revutsky;
Desnianskyi district - st. Leskovskaya (within the streets of Miloslavskaya and Radunskaya), st. Marina Tsvetaeva (within the limits of Nikolay Zakrevsky St. and Vladimir Mayakovsky Avenue)
Dneprovsky district - Amvrosia Buchma blvd., 2-10;
Obolonsky district - st. Peter Kalnyshevsky, 1-5;
Pechersky district - st. Catherine Bilokur;
Podolsky district - ave. Stepan Bandera (near Kurenevsky Park);
Svyatoshinsky district - st. Bulgakov, 10-13 / 1;
Shevchenkivskyi district - st. Podvoisky, 2-12.
Sunday November 3
Goloseevsky district - st. Marshal Konev (within the streets of Mikhail Lomonosov and Vasily Kasiyan)
Pechersky district - st. John McCain (within the streets of John Paul II and Chigorin);
Shevchenkivskyi district - st. Tatar, 32-38.
